<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="laugh-v">laugh <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /lɑːf/    美 /læf/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-vi-vt">1.★ <strong>vi &amp; vt 笑：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>laugh at</strong> a joke
听了笑话发笑</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>laugh heartily
开怀大笑</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>no laughing matter</strong>
不是闹着玩的事</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Doctors have discovered that people who laugh a lot live longer! 
医生发现笑得多的人更长寿。</p><footer> 译林⑥ – 1</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="a-laughing-stock">a laughing stock</h3>
<p>1.<strong>笑料；笑柄</strong>  </p>
<h3 id="laugh-at">laugh at</h3>
<p>1.<strong>嘲笑：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She laughed at me and said that I was not grown-up enough. 
她笑话我，说我不够成熟。</p><footer>人教⑥ – 3</footer></div></div>